<script>
    document.getElementById("demo").innerHTML = "My First JavaScript"
</script>

<!--JavaScript Functions and Evebnts
 A JavaScript Function is a block of JavaScirpt Code, than can be execute when called for.

For example. a function can be called when a event occurs, like when the user clicks a button.-->

<!--JavaScript in <head> or <body>
    
You can place any number of scripts in an HTML document.

Script can be places in the <body>, or in the <head> section of an HTML page, or in both.
    
JavaScript in <head>

In this example, a JavaScript function is placed in the <head> section of an HTML page.

The Function is invoked (called) when button is clicked:-->
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<script>
function myFunction() {
  document.getElementById("demo").innerHTML = "Paragraph changed.";
}
</script>
</head>
<body>
<h2>Demo JavaScript in Head</h2>

<p id="demo">A Paragraph</p>
<button type="button" onclick="myFunction()">Try it</button>

</body>
</html>